author: AFP
title: Wuhan's 'wet markets' struggle after virus lockdown
description: Shut down during the lengthy quarantine that sealed off Wuhan until April 8, the city's wet markets are now fighting for survival as customers have not been rushing back.
content:
WUHAN: At a large food market in the Chinese city of Wuhan, signs forbid the selling of wild animals and live fowl, while announcements calling for "victory" over COVID-19 play on a loop from speakers.
China's "wet markets" have been slammed internationally … [+3692 chars]
